01:45:03.763 --> 01:45:07.308
At least we don't have to worry
about any more kids.

01:45:07.433 --> 01:45:10.686
Not the way I've been
performing in bed lately.

01:45:11.437 --> 01:45:15.649
Karl, it's just temporary.

01:45:19.820 --> 01:45:23.949
You think you should see another doctor
about those headaches?

01:45:25.159 --> 01:45:29.372
Maybe when this new trial is over,
things will get better.

01:45:36.671 --> 01:45:40.132
I better get going.

01:45:50.726 --> 01:45:53.354
Trial will never end.

01:45:57.650 --> 01:46:00.611
Trial is never going to end.

01:46:02.613 --> 01:46:04.448
Never.

01:46:35.730 --> 01:46:38.357
Please, shut up.

01:48:49.739 --> 01:48:51.991
Daddy!

01:48:57.705 --> 01:49:01.083
Yes, darling? I'm here.

01:49:03.586 --> 01:49:07.256
Daddy! The baby's crying.

01:49:10.634 --> 01:49:13.554
Go back to bed, darling.

01:49:16.223 --> 01:49:19.393
I'll take care of our baby.

01:50:08.901 --> 01:50:11.737
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

01:50:19.870 --> 01:50:22.123
Hello, Karl.

01:50:22.623 --> 01:50:26.168
- Pierce, how are you?
- Getting older.

01:50:26.293 --> 01:50:28.754
Friend of yours.

01:50:29.588 --> 01:50:33.259
Emmanuel. How are you?

01:50:33.467 --> 01:50:36.012
I'm still digging in the dirt.

01:50:37.596 --> 01:50:41.100
I pass by Bakersfield
on my way to my fishing spot.

01:50:41.225 --> 01:50:44.228
I stopped by there about...

01:50:44.353 --> 01:50:47.231
a year ago, looking for you.

01:50:47.356 --> 01:50:51.485
I hear there was a white man looking
for me. I figured it was you.

01:50:51.610 --> 01:50:53.654
They want you now, Mr. Hettinger.

01:50:53.779 --> 01:50:56.449
How are they treating you, Karl?

01:50:56.574 --> 01:50:58.659
Fine.

01:51:01.662 --> 01:51:03.831
Just fine.

01:51:05.875 --> 01:51:10.755
How many times have you testified
to these events over the years?

01:51:11.005 --> 01:51:14.467
Maybe eight times.

01:51:15.259 --> 01:51:17.094
I don't quite remember.

01:51:17.219 --> 01:51:20.890
And when you testify, does it bring
the events back to your mind?

01:51:21.015 --> 01:51:25.811
Sometimes it fades away between trials.

01:51:26.270 --> 01:51:28.522
Sometimes...

01:51:32.401 --> 01:51:34.570
then...

01:51:37.531 --> 01:51:38.908
I'm sorry.

01:51:39.033 --> 01:51:42.661
Could you repeat that question,
please, sir? I can't...

01:51:42.787 --> 01:51:44.538
I'm going to renew my motion...

01:51:44.663 --> 01:51:47.416
that this witness'
entire testimony be stricken.

01:51:47.541 --> 01:51:51.879
Will counsel for both defendants
please approach the bench?

01:52:03.933 --> 01:52:06.018
All right, off the record, Your Honor...

01:52:06.143 --> 01:52:11.190
let me read a subpoenaed
psychiatric report on my chief witness.

01:52:11.357 --> 01:52:13.859
"Mr. Hettinger is undergoing
severe depression...

01:52:13.984 --> 01:52:16.570
formerly masked by
a compulsive need to steal.

01:52:16.696 --> 01:52:19.281
His former thefts were
obviously a crying-out for help...

01:52:19.407 --> 01:52:20.658
a desire to be punished.

01:52:20.783 --> 01:52:23.244
He's experiencing
overwhelming unconscious guilt...

01:52:23.369 --> 01:52:27.206
which he associates with not having
done his duty the night of the murder.

01:52:27.331 --> 01:52:30.292
Suicidal behavior
is a distinct possibility."

01:52:30.418 --> 01:52:32.253
Would the defense
like the jury to hear...

01:52:32.378 --> 01:52:34.880
what Mr. Hettinger has suffered
the past seven years?

01:52:35.006 --> 01:52:37.633
Your Honor, the question is
whether or not Hettinger...

01:52:37.758 --> 01:52:39.885
is mentally competent at this time.

01:52:40.011 --> 01:52:43.097
His testimony of seven years ago
is no longer relevant.

01:52:43.222 --> 01:52:45.266
You may step down.

01:52:49.937 --> 01:52:52.314
I believe he is competent.

01:52:52.440 --> 01:52:55.151
Your Honor,
I'm gonna call Gregory Powell right now.

01:52:55.276 --> 01:52:56.819
I object, Your Honor.

01:52:56.944 --> 01:52:59.488
He must not be allowed
to take the stand at this time.

01:52:59.613 --> 01:53:01.282
This is a jailhouse legal trick.

01:53:01.407 --> 01:53:04.118
I know it, you know it,
the defense knows it.

01:53:04.243 --> 01:53:06.871
Mr. Powell will be allowed to testify.

01:53:06.996 --> 01:53:11.083
A trier of fact cannot draw an inference
about what a witness will or will not do.

01:53:11.208 --> 01:53:12.335
Call your witness.

01:53:12.460 --> 01:53:16.547
- May I stand with my client, Your Honor?
- You may.

01:53:23.971 --> 01:53:27.058
Call Gregory Ulas Powell.

01:53:54.919 --> 01:53:57.713
Do you solemnly swear
that the testimony you shall give...

01:53:57.838 --> 01:53:59.799
in the cause now pending
in this court...

01:53:59.924 --> 01:54:03.928
shall be the truth, the whole truth, and
nothing but the truth, so help you God?

01:54:04.053 --> 01:54:05.971
I do.

01:54:21.320 --> 01:54:24.323
Mr. Powell, how many times
did you shoot Officer Campbell?

01:54:24.448 --> 01:54:27.076
I repeat my objection to this
as being asked in bad faith.

01:54:27.201 --> 01:54:30.204
Overruled.

01:54:42.925 --> 01:54:47.513
Based on the Fifth Amendment
to the Constitution of the United States...

01:54:47.638 --> 01:54:52.393
I refuse to answer that question
on the grounds it may incriminate me.

01:54:53.561 --> 01:54:58.816
- I have no further questions.
- You may step down, Mr. Powell.

01:56:36.080 --> 01:56:41.252
- How's my landscape designer?
- Your gardener is fine.

01:56:43.921 --> 01:56:46.048
Couldn't be better.

01:56:46.173 --> 01:56:48.634
The beer's nice and cold.

01:56:52.054 --> 01:56:54.390
I was wondering...

01:56:54.765 --> 01:56:57.685
if you'd mind if I took a real job.

01:56:59.311 --> 01:57:01.105
What job?

01:57:01.230 --> 01:57:05.276
I got an offer to go to work...

01:57:05.985 --> 01:57:11.240
at a big, commercial nursery.

01:57:11.365 --> 01:57:13.451
You did?

01:57:19.373 --> 01:57:22.418
I'd have to supervise 30 men, so...

01:57:22.543 --> 01:57:25.046
Karl. It's terrific!

01:57:25.171 --> 01:57:29.675
You could supervise 30 men or 300,
for that matter.

01:57:29.800 --> 01:57:34.138
- Why didn't you tell me?
- It's in Bakersfield.

01:57:34.555 --> 01:57:36.432
Way...

01:57:36.557 --> 01:57:39.894
Near the onion field?

01:57:41.020 --> 01:57:44.273
Near the onion field, yeah.

01:57:46.984 --> 01:57:49.320
It's real work.

01:57:49.445 --> 01:57:51.864
It's a good job.

01:57:56.077 --> 01:57:58.913
I think you should take it.

01:57:59.038 --> 01:58:01.540
What do you think?

01:58:05.044 --> 01:58:08.047
I think I should take it, too.

01:58:10.925 --> 01:58:15.304
Mr. Powell, congratulations.
I hear they gave you a parole date.

01:58:15.429 --> 01:58:18.015
- 1983, I hear.
- Yes.

01:58:18.140 --> 01:58:20.935
Could you turn that down, please?

01:58:23.187 --> 01:58:26.899
Mr. Powell, could you talk to me
about my appeal?

01:58:27.024 --> 01:58:30.986
They say you got one of
the best legal minds in the yard.

01:58:31.112 --> 01:58:32.363
I'd be glad to.

01:58:32.488 --> 01:58:35.574
I could teach you some law,
if you were a willing student.

01:58:35.700 --> 01:58:38.828
- You could?
- It would be my pleasure.

01:58:38.953 --> 01:58:42.998
First, I gotta put the finishing touches
on this letter to my family.

01:58:43.124 --> 01:58:46.752
Seems like everyone wants me
to run their affairs.

01:58:47.753 --> 01:58:50.464
You got a family, son?

01:58:52.967 --> 01:58:54.802
Very important, family.

01:58:54.927 --> 01:58:57.346
It's the foundation
and wellspring of all that's...

01:58:57.471 --> 01:59:00.766
productive and wholesome
in our social system.

01:59:07.940 --> 01:59:10.776
Do you ever play that game?

01:59:10.985 --> 01:59:14.447
At my age? No way.

01:59:16.407 --> 01:59:19.535
I hear you
and your old friend Powell are...

01:59:19.660 --> 01:59:22.997
going to be getting out in a few years.

01:59:24.498 --> 01:59:27.585
Are you going to stay out this time?

01:59:28.210 --> 01:59:30.254
My man...

01:59:31.505 --> 01:59:34.675
I was born for a prison yard.

01:59:54.987 --> 01:59:59.867
- How do you like your bacon, Mom?
- Served to me.

02:00:00.576 --> 02:00:03.412
This is my idea of Mother's Day.

02:00:03.537 --> 02:00:05.790
No kids...

02:00:05.915 --> 02:00:08.834
and a cook who's gonna
double as a dishwasher.

02:00:08.959 --> 02:00:12.004
This can go too far, you know.

02:00:12.505 --> 02:00:14.256
Guess what?

02:00:14.382 --> 02:00:18.094
The other day,
I went driving by the onion field...

02:00:18.219 --> 02:00:21.472
and you'll never guess what happened.

02:00:21.597 --> 02:00:27.395
As I was driving by, this ad came
on the radio for the Black Watch Pipers.

02:00:29.397 --> 02:00:31.816
Can you imagine?

02:00:32.233 --> 02:00:37.446
As I was driving by,
bagpipe music came over the radio.

02:00:40.157 --> 02:00:42.034
And?

02:00:43.160 --> 02:00:45.329
And it's...

02:00:45.454 --> 02:00:48.666
pretty nice music.

02:00:51.752 --> 02:00:56.257
If you give it a chance, lassie.

02:01:00.094 --> 02:01:03.347
Enough of this drudgery.
I'll drudge later.

02:01:03.472 --> 02:01:04.974
Come on.

02:01:05.099 --> 02:01:07.643
- Where are we going?
- Come on.

02:01:07.768 --> 02:01:09.645
- We're going to go swimming.
- No.

02:01:09.770 --> 02:01:13.774
- No! Karl! Karl, it's too cold.
- It's warm in the sleeping bag.

02:01:13.899 --> 02:01:15.943
No!

02:01:16.193 --> 02:01:18.612
No! Karl, no!

02:01:22.283 --> 02:01:24.326
Karl, look.

02:01:24.452 --> 02:01:26.746
The little fish...

02:01:26.871 --> 02:01:29.331
They're kissing us.

02:01:29.915 --> 02:01:32.668
Those are bluegills.
They're just hungry.

02:01:32.793 --> 02:01:36.464
They nibble at everything
that comes into the water.

02:01:36.922 --> 02:01:42.261
- Damn it, Karl, I say they're kissing us.
- Okay, Helen.

02:01:42.720 --> 02:01:45.097
Okay, they're kissing us.

02:03:17.565 --> 02:03:20.693
- Hello.
- Hello.

02:03:20.818 --> 02:03:23.988
- You're a good piper.
- Thanks.

02:03:24.113 --> 02:03:27.324
I'm not that good.
I don't think I'll win a medal or nothing.

02:03:27.450 --> 02:03:28.784
You may.

02:03:28.909 --> 02:03:32.663
My son won a silver medal here once,
a long time ago.

02:03:32.788 --> 02:03:35.875
You must know about the bagpipes then.

02:03:36.000 --> 02:03:39.462
My people were from Scotland,
and so were my husband's.

02:03:39.587 --> 02:03:43.132
But I always wanted my boy
to play piano.

02:03:43.257 --> 02:03:47.970
- The pipes are so boisterous.
- No. That's the kind of brave music it is.

02:03:48.095 --> 02:03:51.098
I hope your son stayed
with the bagpipes.

02:03:51.557 --> 02:03:53.309
Forever.

02:03:53.434 --> 02:03:57.146
I think I'll play the bagpipes
as long as I live.

02:03:57.271 --> 02:04:00.566
I think that's a lovely idea.
